{
  "stem": "22979.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I got-- I was lucky.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was assigned to a special unit, about 300 girls of us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And this unit was called Canada.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We were assigned to do-- to sort the clothing after people-- you know-- people still didn't go to the gas chambers in 1942, because they were not built.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "In 1942, you know, it was already in one barrack the piles of-- of their luggage and the clothing, which we undressed.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we-- our job was to sort the clothing, and you know, separate the underwear, panties, and so on, and bundle them neatly in 10 in a package.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then, you know, the other barrack was where we loaded those packages.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "When the transport came, this time to Auschwitz, not to Birkenau-- we were still in Auschwitz-- those packages, we had to [NON-ENGLISH]-- take to those empty cattle cars where they brought the new arrivals.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And on the-- I mean, outside, on those cars, were letters, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Winter help for the families who have their son on the front.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So this Jewish clothing for-- from us, which they brought, you know, in quotation 'to work,' went back to Germany, warmed the families, which actually sent us to our deaths.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Irony was-- irony.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But you know, some of the-- us, right in the beginning-- very brave girls.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I didn't do it right in the beginning-- wrote a little, because we had everything-- pencils.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were paper, writing paper-- wrote down when the SS didn't look, you know, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "How did they write that?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Jewish clothing from concentration camp-- stacked in in between, because they didn't open-- they didn't even think of it at this time, writing this.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we hoped somebody got it in the pocket, in these, when they got the nice clothing.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
